Compliance history
==================

Mantis incorporates substantial verbatim ports of Apache-2.0-licensed
prompt and agent files from Hacker Bob (https://github.com/vmihalis/hacker-bob).
For an interval prior to 2026-05-25, this repository declared the
`Apache-2.0 OR MIT` license in README and `Cargo.toml` but did not
carry the actual LICENSE files on disk, did not reproduce the upstream
Hacker Bob NOTICE verbatim per Apache-2.0 §4(d), and did not carry
per-file change notices on the ported files per §4(b). This was a
license-compliance failure, not a contested-attribution dispute — the
attribution was already documented in NOTICE and CONTRAST.md, but the
formal §4 mechanics were incomplete.

Remediated on 2026-05-25 in the following commits on `main`:

  53d9b4f  Merge #18 — add LICENSE-APACHE + LICENSE-MIT (§4(a)),
           propagate upstream NOTICE verbatim (§4(d)), and correct the
           prior wording in this NOTICE that mis-stated "no source
           ported" — agent and role prompts are verbatim ports with
           tool-name renames.
  c59fdba  Merge #19 — add §4(b) "prominent notice of changes"
           headers to 35 ported files in `plugin/claude-code/agents/`
           and `prompts/roles/`.

No source code was withheld during the gap window; the violation was
the missing license texts and missing per-file change notices, not
concealment of derivation. Grateful acknowledgement to Hacker Bob and
its maintainer for the upstream work that made Mantis possible.

